'''Doris Meth Srinivasan''' is a Professor of German origin, specialising in Indolological studies and she has authored more than 75 publications. <ref name=story>{{cite web|title=Doris Srinivasan|url=http://www.stonybrook.edu/commcms/india/people/dorissrinivasan.html|publisher=storybook.edu|accessdate=28 August 2013}}</ref>  She was curator of South and South East Asian arts Nelson-Atkins Museum in Kansas City, Missouri.<ref name=art>{{cite web|title=Doris Meth Srinivasan|url=http://islamic-arts.org/author/doris-srinivasan/|publisher=Islamic Arts and Architecture|accessdate=28 August 2013}}</ref>
==Early life==
Doris Meth Srinivasan was born at Schwabisch Gmund, Germany and received PhD from University of Pennsylvania and her desertion was "Concept of Cow in Rigveda".<ref name=story/> She taught mainly South Asian Art, Religion at various universities like Columbia University and Barnard College,George Washington University, George Mason University etc.<ref name=story/>
==Publications==
*Many Heads, Arms and eyes: Origin, Meaning and Forms of Multiplicity in Indian Art (1997)
*Mathura : The Cultural Heritage (1989)<ref name=story/>
*Vishnu 
